modules.description: This module defines the structure of messages received via Zulip's real-time events API, including sender details, message content, and associated flags. It provides functions to inspect message properties such as whether it was starred, privately sent, or directed at the current user, and allows constructing replies based on message context. Concrete use cases include filtering messages by recipient type, generating sender mentions, and sending targeted replies in event-driven bots or real-time messaging applications.

This module handles sending, editing, and deleting messages in a messaging system, supporting both stream and private messages. It works with message destinations defined by stream names or IDs, email addresses, or user IDs, and provides functions for uploading files as part of messages. Concrete use cases include sending a message to a specific stream topic, uploading a file attachment, or editing an existing message's content or topic.

This module handles real-time event interaction with Zulip's API, offering functions to process message streams, respond to commands, and manage event queues. It works with message and event data types, enabling use cases like building event-driven bots that react to direct messages or specific commands in real time. Low-level functions allow direct queue management and event polling for custom event handling logic.

This module provides an interface to interact with the Zulip messaging platform, handling message and event operations. It supports sending, editing, and deleting messages to streams or private conversations, uploading file attachments, and processing real-time events via Zulip's API. Use cases include automating message posting to specific topics, building event-driven bots that respond to direct messages or commands, and managing message content and attachments programmatically.
